{"title":"Wolf Tooth GnarWolf V2 Chain Guides Add Colors, Drop Price","link":"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-gnarwolf-chainguide-v2/","date":1723295849000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-ISCG-mount-2-1536x1025.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1025\" alt=\"wolf tooth components gnarwolf ISCG05 chainguide on a mountain bike.\" /></p>\n<p>Whoa…it’s been seven years since the Wolf Tooth Components <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-components-stops-drop-w-new-gnarwolf-chain-guide/\">GnarWolf chain guides debuted</a>, so it was about time for an update…or was it?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The original introduced a shim-free chainline adjustment, using a simple ovalized locking collet that let you fine-tune the guide’s position over your chain. It accommodates chain lines from 45-51mm.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And the ISCG-05 version used a simple one-bolt height adjustment to fit chainrings from 28 to 34 teeth.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-ISCG-mount-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1140\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-ISCG-mount-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"wolf tooth components gnarwolf ISCG05 chainguide.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-ISCG-mount-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-ISCG-mount-297x132.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-ISCG-mount-1536x684.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-ISCG-mount-120x53.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-ISCG-mount-768x342.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-ISCG-mount-2048x912.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new GnarWolf V2 does all those things, but simplifies the design of the guide (and adds a couple of holes to give mud and crud more exit points) and adds four color options – yellow, orange, blue, and purple. Or stick with classic black.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>They’ve also dropped the price by $15, now just $49.95 for the ISCG-05 model in all black. Additional/color guides are $4.95.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-brazeon-mount-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"901\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-brazeon-mount-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"wolf tooth components gnarwolf braze-on chainguide.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-brazeon-mount-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-brazeon-mount-297x105.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-brazeon-mount-1536x541.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-brazeon-mount-120x42.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-brazeon-mount-768x270.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wolftooth-gnar-guide-v2-chainguide-brazeon-mount-2048x721.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The braze-on mount has the same color choices and is also $49.95. It mounts to any standard front-derailleur braze-on mount and has three bolt holes to fit chainrings from 28 to 34 teeth, too.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.wolftoothcomponents.com/collections/chainguides\" target=\"_blank\">WolfToothComponents.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-gnarwolf-chainguide-v2/\">Wolf Tooth GnarWolf V2 Chain Guides Add Colors, Drop Price</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"ef3e5f46a1e35f5da25c9b5abe11a61a35437f7e2bb759f978f263e4c49ac35f","category":"Cycling"}